#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.43:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavagga "
msgstr "5. Overflowing Merit, With Verses "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 43. Tatiyaabhisandasutta → tatiyaasaṅkheyyasuttaṃ (bj) | abhisanda or sayhaka 3 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Tatiyaabhisandasutta "
msgstr "43. Overflowing Merit (3rd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.43:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā, kusalābhisandā, sukhassāhārā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurture happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.43:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.43:2.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …. "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.402, sc3
msgctxt "sn55.43:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn55.43:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro. "
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.43:3.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurture happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.43:4.1"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi puññābhisandehi kusalābhisandehi samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ: "
msgstr "When a noble disciple has these four kinds of overflowing merit and goodness, it’s not easy to measure how much merit they have by saying that "

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.2"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro’ti. "
msgstr "this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness. "

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.43:4.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.5"
msgid "satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.1"
msgid "“Yo puññakāmo kusale patiṭṭhito, "
msgstr "“One who desires merit, grounded in the skillful, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.2"
msgid "Bhāveti maggaṃ amatassa pattiyā; "
msgstr "develops the eightfold path for realizing the deathless. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.3"
msgid "So dhammasārādhigamo khaye rato, "
msgstr "Once they’ve reached the heart of the teaching, delighting in ending, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: maccurājāgamanasmin”ti → maccurājā gamissatīti (bj) | maccurājāgamasminti (s1-3) | maccurāja gamissatīti (pts1) | maccujarākampisminti (mr)
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.4"
msgid "Na vedhati maccurājāgamanasmin”ti. "
msgstr "they don’t tremble at the approach of the King of Death.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
